# FooterLinks Component Rules

## Overview
Rules and patterns for the FooterLinks component (`src/components/molecules/FooterLinks.tsx`)

## Purpose
Renders footer sections with links in a responsive grid layout

## Rules

### Core Requirements
- ✅ **Data Source:** Import from `@/constants/footer` using `FOOTER_SECTIONS`
- ✅ **Responsive Grid:** Use `grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-4` for mobile-first design
- ✅ **Spacing:** Consistent gap (`gap-8`) and section spacing (`space-y-2`)
- ✅ **Typography:** Section titles use `text-lg font-semibold mb-3`
- ✅ **Link Styling:** Gray text with brand color hover (`text-gray-700 hover:text-[#8a0028]`)
- ✅ **Nested Mapping:** Handle both sections and links with proper keys
- ✅ **Semantic HTML:** Use proper heading (`h3`) and list (`ul`, `li`) structure

## Code Template
```typescript
import Link from "next/link";
import { FOOTER_SECTIONS } from "@/constants/footer";

export function FooterLinks() {
  return (
    <div className="grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-4 gap-8 w-full">
      {FOOTER_SECTIONS.map((section) => (
        <div key={section.title}>
          <h3 className="text-lg font-semibold mb-3">{section.title}</h3>
          <ul className="space-y-2">
            {section.links.map((l) => (
              <li key={l.label}>
                <Link href={l.href} className="text-gray-700 hover:text-[#8a0028]">
                  {l.label}
                </Link>
              </li>
            ))}
          </ul>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>
  );
}

export default FooterLinks;
```

## Implementation Details

### Data Dependencies
- Import: `FOOTER_SECTIONS` from `@/constants/footer`
